Global Hospital Gowns Market - Industry Overview

A hospital gown is a form of protective clothing used in medical settings to safeguard the wearer from infectious diseases and exposure to contaminated liquids or materials. It is often used in conjunction with PPE kits to provide comprehensive protection against infections. According to Asian Development Bank, The global market for PPE in the health sector was estimated to be worth 2.5 billion in 2018, out of which suits or coveralls has 22% market share. The global hospital gowns market is a crucial segment of the healthcare apparel industry, focusing on the production and supply of gowns used in medical settings to maintain hygiene and protect both patients and healthcare providers. Hospital gowns are essential for infection control, procedural support, and patient comfort. The market includes various types of gowns such as disposable, reusable, and surgical gowns, each designed to meet specific healthcare needs.

